2671 parserDynaML.CompleteAssociationLists(&vmeasurementsTotal, &associatedSL, &associatedML);
2672 if (!p.g.quiet)

2677 imp_file << "Done." << std::endl;
2678 }
2679 catch (const XMLInteropException& e) {

2681 imp_file << std::endl << "- Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
2682 imp_file.close();
2683 return EXIT_FAILURE;
2684 }

2686 try {
2687 if (!p.g.quiet)
2688 {
2689 std::cout << "+ Serialising association lists... ";

2691 }
2692 imp_file << "+ Serialising association lists... ";
2693 parserDynaML.SerialiseAsl(p.i.asl_file, &associatedSL);
2694 parserDynaML.SerialiseAml(p.i.aml_file, &associatedML);
2695 if (!p.g.quiet)
2696 {
2697 std::cout << "Done." << std::endl;
2698 std::cout.flush();
2699 }
2700 imp_file << "Done." << std::endl;
2701 }
2702 catch (const XMLInteropException& e) {
2703 std::cout << "- Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
2704 imp_file << std::endl << "- Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
2705 imp_file.close();
2706 return EXIT_FAILURE;
2707 }
2708 }
2709
2710 // Create binary station file.
2711 // Binary station file can be serialised without measurements
2712 if (stnCount > 0)
2713 {
2714 try {
2715 if (!vstationsTotal.empty())
2716 {
2717 if (!p.g.quiet)
2718 {
2719 std::cout << "+ Serialising binary station file " << leafStr<std::string>(p.i.bst_file) << "... ";

2723
2724 parserDynaML.SerialiseBst(
2725 p.i.bst_file, ((vdnaStnPtr*) &vstationsTotal), &vunusedStations,
2726 vinput_file_meta, (p.i.flag_unused_stn ? true : false));
2727 if (!p.g.quiet)
2728 {
2729 std::cout << "Done." << std::endl;
2730 std::cout.flush();
2731 }
2732 imp_file << "Done." << std::endl;
2733 }
2734 }
2735 catch (const XMLInteropException& e) {
2736 std::cout << "- Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
2737 imp_file << std::endl << "- Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
2738 imp_file.close();
2739 return EXIT_FAILURE;
2740 }
2741 }
2742
2743 // Create binary measurement file.
2744 // Binary measurement file can be serialised without stations
2745 if (msrCount > 0)
2746 {
2747 try {
2748 if (!vmeasurementsTotal.empty())
2749 {
2750 if (!p.g.quiet)
2751 {
2752 std::cout << "+ Serialising binary measurement file " << leafStr<std::string>(p.i.bms_file) << "... ";
2753 std::cout.flush();
2754 }
2755 imp_file << "+ Serialising binary measurement file " << leafStr<std::string>(p.i.bms_file) << "... ";
2756

2758 p.i.bms_file, ((vdnaMsrPtr*) &vmeasurementsTotal),
2759 vinput_file_meta);

2761 {

2763 std::cout.flush();

2770 imp_file << std::endl << "- Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
2771 imp_file.close();
2772 return EXIT_FAILURE;
2773 }
2774 }

2776 // Export ASL and AML to text if required
2777 if (measurements_mapped)
2778 {

2780 if (p.i.export_asl_file)
2781 {

2783 {

2800 imp_file.close();
2801 return EXIT_FAILURE;

2804 try {
2805 if (p.i.export_aml_file)
2806 {

2808 {

2810 std::cout.flush();

2813 parserDynaML.SerialiseAmlTextFile(p.i.bms_file, p.i.aml_file, &associatedML, &associatedSL, (vdnaStnPtr*) &vstationsTotal);

2820 }

2824 imp_file << std::endl << "- Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
2825 imp_file.close();
2826 return EXIT_FAILURE;
2827 }

2829 if (p.i.test_integrity)
2830 {
2831 if (!p.g.quiet)
2832 {
2833 std::cout << "+ Testing internal integrity of ASL, AML and binary files... ";
2834 std::cout.flush();
2835 }
2836 std::ifstream binaryMS(p.i.bms_file.c_str(), std::ios::in | std::ios::binary | std::ifstream::ate);
2837 if (!binaryMS.good())
2838 {
2839 std::cout << std::endl << "- Could not open binary file for reading." << std::endl;
2840 imp_file << std::endl << "- Could not open binary file for reading." << std::endl;
2841 imp_file.close();
2842 return EXIT_FAILURE;
2843 }
2844 // get size, then go back to beginning
2845 size_t sFileSize = (size_t)binaryMS.tellg();
2846 binaryMS.seekg(0, std::ios::beg);
2847
2848 measurement_t measRecord;
2849
2850 UINT32 amlcount, amlindex, msr;
2851 for (stn=0; stn<stnCount; stn++)
2852 {
2853 amlcount = associatedSL.at(stn).get()->GetAssocMsrCount();
2854
2855 // The following is to be used when reading from binary file
2856 for (msr=0; msr<amlcount; msr++)
2857 {
2858 amlindex = associatedSL.at(stn).get()->GetAMLStnIndex() + msr;
2859 if (associatedML.at(amlindex) * sizeof(measurement_t) >= sFileSize)
2860 {
2861 std::cout << "Error: index " << associatedML.at(amlindex) << " is out of range for the binary file." << std::endl;
2862 continue;
2863 }
2864 binaryMS.seekg(sizeof(UINT32) + associatedML.at(amlindex) * sizeof(measurement_t), std::ios::beg);
2865 binaryMS.read(reinterpret_cast<char *>(&measRecord), sizeof(measurement_t));
2866 }
2867 }
2868 binaryMS.close();
2869 if (!p.g.quiet)
2870 std::cout << "OK." << std::endl;
2871 }
2872 }
2873
2874 try {
2875 // Print measurements to stations table
2876 PrintMeasurementstoStations(&parsemsrTally, &parserDynaML, &p, &associatedSL);
2877 }
2878 catch (const XMLInteropException& e) {

2881 imp_file << std::endl << "- Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
2882 imp_file.close();
2883 return EXIT_FAILURE;

2888 if (p.i.import_block == 1 || p.i.import_network == 1)
2889 {

2892 }
2893 else
2894 {

2897 }
2898
2899 // Export stations and measurements
2900 try {
2901 if (p.i.export_dynaml || p.i.export_dna_files)
2902 ExportStationsandMeasurements(&parserDynaML, p, &imp_file, &vinput_file_meta,
2903 &vstationsTotal, &vmeasurementsTotal, stnCount, msrCount);
2904 }
2905 catch (const XMLInteropException& e) {
2906 std::cout.flush();
2907 std::cout << std::endl << "- Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
2908 imp_file << std::endl << "- Error: " << e.what() << std::endl;
2909 imp_file.close();
2910 return EXIT_FAILURE;
2911 }
2912
2913 if (!userSuppliedSegFile)
2914 p.i.seg_file = "";
2915 if (!userSuppliedBstFile)
2916 p.i.bst_file = "";
2917 if (!userSuppliedBmsFile)
2918 p.i.bms_file = "";
2919
2920 // Look for a project file. If it exists, open and load it.
2921 // Update the import settings.
2922 // Print the project file. If it doesn't exist, it will be created.
2923 CDnaProjectFile projectFile;
2924 if (boost::filesystem::exists(p.g.project_file))
2925 projectFile.LoadProjectFile(p.g.project_file);
2926
2927 projectFile.UpdateSettingsImport(p);
2928 projectFile.UpdateSettingsReftran(p);
2929 projectFile.UpdateSettingsOutput(p);
2930 projectFile.PrintProjectFile();
2931
2932 if (msrCount == 0)
2933 {
2934 std::cout << "- Warning: there are no measurements to process." << std::endl;
2935 imp_file << "- Warning: there are no measurements to process." << std::endl;
2936 }
2937
2938 if (errorCount)
2939 {
2940 if (!p.g.quiet)
2941 std::cout << "- Warning: some files were not parsed - please read the log file for more details." << std::endl;
2942 imp_file << "- Warning: some files were not parsed - please read the log file for more details." << std::endl;
2943 }
2944
2945 // Produce a warning if an ensemble is set as the default reference frame
2946 if (isEpsgWGS84Ensemble(epsgCode))
2947 {
2948 std::stringstream ssEnsembleWarning;
2949 ssEnsembleWarning << std::endl <<
2950 "- Warning: The '" << p.i.reference_frame << "' reference frame set for this project refers to the" << std::endl <<
2951 " \"World Geodetic System 1984 (WGS 84) ensemble\". The WGS 84 ensemble is" << std::endl <<
2952 " only suitable for low accuracy (metre level) positioning and does not" << std::endl <<
2953 " provide for precise transformations to other well-known reference frames." << std::endl <<
2954 " To achieve reliable adjustment results from data on WGS 84, please refer" << std::endl <<
2955 " to \"Configuring import options\" in the DynAdjust User's Guide." << std::endl;
2956 if (!p.g.quiet)
2957 std::cout << ssEnsembleWarning.str();
2958 imp_file << ssEnsembleWarning.str();
2959 }
2960
2961 boost::posix_time::milliseconds elapsed_time(boost::posix_time::milliseconds(time.elapsed().wall/MILLI_TO_NANO));
2962 std::string time_message = formatedElapsedTime<std::string>(&elapsed_time, "+ Total file handling process took ");
2963
2964 if (!p.g.quiet)
2965 std::cout << std::endl << time_message << std::endl;
2966 imp_file << std::endl << time_message << std::endl;
2967
2968 if (stnCount > 0 && msrCount > 0)
2969 {
2970 if (!p.g.quiet)
2971 std::cout << "+ Binary station and measurement files are now ready for processing." << std::endl << std::endl;
2972 imp_file << "+ Binary station and measurement files are now ready for processing." << std::endl << std::endl;
2973 }
2974
2975 imp_file.close();
2976 return PARSE_SUCCESS;
2977}
